Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.53,0:00:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,afternoon, Dr. Hawkins. Yes. Tomorrow's Father's Day. Uh-oh. And your spiritual children are out
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.11,0:00:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there. Oh. I want to give you a card. Oh, thank you. And I wanted to thank you for the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.13,0:00:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and my question is dealing with avoidance of evil. Early you were talking about dealing with what?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.80,0:00:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The avoidance of dealing with evil, correct? In the past, in the past 7th, 8th, and 9th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.24,0:01:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,10th century, Islam had been very successful in achieving high science, math, architecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.62,0:01:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and astronomy, as I perceive it. And for the last thousand years, it's kind of nothing's really
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.80,0:01:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,happened. Yes, it had its high period, yeah. And my question for you is dealing with the perception
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.88,0:01:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of what do you feel is the real reason that Islam has slipped? Is it their influence and power or
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.46,0:01:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,not achieving their high ideals in these areas?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.24,0:01:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I really don't know. It's, you see, don't forget it's factional. It's factional. Islam is factional.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.87,0:01:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Much like the Catholics and the Protestants in Europe, you know, medieval Europe. Where are all
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.46,0:01:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,these little covers come from? And it's factional. Also, Islam is political. People like to think of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.23,0:01:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it as a religion. It's a political religion. It's very political. It states there is the house of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.11,0:02:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Islam and there is the house of Islam. And there is the house of Islam. And there is the house of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.13,0:02:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,war. The house of Islam is us and the house of war is everyone else. So, it's very egocentric to a degree, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.47,0:02:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there dissatisfaction in Islam because of their lack of influence in the world as it once was today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.76,0:02:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. You're asking me a lot of political questions. My, you know, the principle of hegemony, hegemony.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.19,0:02:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's the name of my writing? Hawkins? Oh, yeah. I can't handle all these covers. I don't know. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.26,0:02:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.26,0:02:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't handle all these covers like this. There is the, I view it as primitive. Hegemony, hegemony is part of animal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.48,0:02:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to be the dominant alpha wolf. You don't see religions acting any different than a wolf pack.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.12,0:03:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my hill. I'm the dominant one. And this other wolf pack wants to come in. And so we will kill them and drive them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that different?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.92,0:03:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No different. So it's the dominance of the animal ego to dominate, to be king of the hill, to be the alpha male.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.83,0:03:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's unimpressive from a spiritual viewpoint and why the Sufis calibrate so much higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the Sufis transcend all that, you know, lower side of human nature really, see? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.35,0:03:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.76,0:03:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If a person wants to be an Islamic, I tell them become a Sufi and avoid all that politicalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.14,0:04:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins. I don't really have a question. I just wanted to express my gratitude to you and Susan and ask for a blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.86,0:04:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.14,0:04:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm asking for your blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.14,0:04:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Oh, I thought you were asking me a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.14,0:04:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.14,0:04:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God bless you, my love.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.45,0:04:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.45,0:04:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Be passionate for God. That's what...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.65,0:04:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.07,0:04:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.07,0:04:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Question. When we contemplate and meditate, at least for the earlier students, right now when I contemplate,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.26,0:05:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the I which is witnessing the silence is still the I, the ego. It doesn't seem to be I, the awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.26,0:05:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you go from I being the ego to I, the awareness when you are contemplating?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.65,0:05:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. From self with a small S to self with a big S.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.79,0:05:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.79,0:05:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Yeah. It isn't so much what you do as what you let go of. As you let go of the self with a small S as being a reality, an intrinsic reality, what you do is you surrender the small self to the large self.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.46,0:05:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And all spiritual endeavor is really aligned with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.49,0:05:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.78,0:05:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization of the presence of God within is the consequence of removing anything that would be in its way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.13,0:05:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, the small self is dissolved into the greater self.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.60,0:06:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So we let go identification with the ego, which presumes that it is the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.48,0:06:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They just sign it right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.99,0:06:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.47,0:06:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So all the spiritual techniques are devised to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.47,0:06:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer, supplications, karma yoga, selfless service.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.10,0:06:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, be helpful to life without looking for any payback.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.10,0:06:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You see a little beetle on his back flying with his feet in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.68,0:06:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you put him on his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.48,0:06:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see a hungry kitten.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You put some food out for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.48,0:06:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You see a dog that's lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.70,0:06:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes dogs will bark.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.70,0:06:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one that barks near me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.70,0:06:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll go out and I'll say, you really don't have to bark.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.70,0:06:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not all by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.70,0:06:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And he stops barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.70,0:06:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He's lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.98,0:07:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants some kind of contact with some other being.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.21,0:07:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I discovered that just going out, even if I tell him you're being a bad dog, please stop barking, he'll stop barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.21,0:07:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all he wants is that sort of human companionship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.21,0:07:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say to him, if you don't stop, I'm going to call the police, he'll stop barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.30,0:07:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I say to him, if you stop barking, I'm going to call the police, he stops barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.38,0:07:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So he wants that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.38,0:07:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.76,0:07:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That dog wants to hear a human voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.76,0:07:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess the folks tie him out and go to town, you know, and leave him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.76,0:07:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And pretty soon, woof, woof.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.76,0:07:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Woof, I'm lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.76,0:07:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So I read it that he's lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.76,0:07:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And no matter what I say to him, he stops woofing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.50,0:07:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do that psychically.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.33,0:07:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to do that psychically.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.33,0:07:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Picture yourself leaving your body and going as a lovingness to the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.33,0:07:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And saying, sweetheart, I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.33,0:07:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And hugging the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.33,0:08:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And seeing that he's lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.33,0:08:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dog will stop barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.33,0:08:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You can actually leave the body and go to the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.33,0:08:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dog's spirit will get a warm, okay feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.39,0:08:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.42,0:08:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you bless me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.06,0:08:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.13,0:08:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.73,0:08:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You can send your spirit to the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.73,0:08:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, oh, I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.73,0:08:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're adorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.73,0:08:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're such a sweet dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.73,0:08:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dog will stop barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.34,0:08:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to thank you first for your dedication to us as a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.34,0:08:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And wanted to ask you if you would please chant one om with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.34,0:08:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't you do the om?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.63,0:08:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.63,0:08:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to do an om today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.63,0:08:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.63,0:08:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody wants to do an om.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.46,0:09:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Om.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.19,0:09:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My voice is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.14,0:09:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.38,0:09:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.38,0:09:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.38,0:09:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.98,0:09:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.57,0:09:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.92,0:09:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Today you spoke about the declaration to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.18,0:09:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.18,0:09:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please talk more about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.18,0:10:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes one sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.55,0:10:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To be the second.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.90,0:10:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Make up a sentence that covers what your intention is and how you align your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.82,0:10:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then make that as a formal declaration to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.19,0:10:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We do that at the start of every lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.46,0:10:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Glory be to thee, O Lord, most high.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.50,0:10:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're acknowledging Almighty God as the most high.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.30,0:10:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All power and glory be to thee, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.81,0:10:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Most high.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.81,0:10:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.96,0:10:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So by acknowledging divinity, you're already making a declaration that you acknowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.34,0:10:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,their divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.34,0:10:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Krishna says, those who commit to me become mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.44,0:10:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The Psalms say, those who call upon me are mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.27,0:11:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So take advantage of that truth and you belong to God once you acknowledge that he is your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.64,0:11:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.31,0:11:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Krishna says, those who call upon me are mine and are divine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.31,0:11:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So take advantage of that truth and you belong to God once you acknowledge that he is your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.82,0:11:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.82,0:11:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're acknowledging divinity as your God and you're telling us to are mine and are
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.82,0:11:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,dear to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.78,0:11:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Which psalm is it, 29, 19 or is it 19?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.78,0:11:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.78,0:11:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It says the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.90,0:11:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who rest their head upon me are mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.90,0:11:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.90,0:11:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's transformative to make that declaration.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.90,0:11:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you my memory is something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.64,0:11:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,29th Psalm or 19th.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.64,0:11:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.49,0:11:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is how can one transcend what still appears to be a duality of God imminent
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.84,0:11:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and transcendent?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.84,0:11:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.59,0:11:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,God knows what God knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.59,0:11:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows that God knows what He knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.00,0:11:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows that God knows what He knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.00,0:11:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows that God knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.60,0:12:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows what He knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.60,0:12:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're worshiping God, you know that all the things that Он knows are the same
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.60,0:12:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How can one transcend what still appears to be a duality of God eminent and transcendent?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.01,0:12:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's not a duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.53,0:12:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just a nominalization, just semantic, just semantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.18,0:12:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.72,0:12:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,God transcendent is the traditional God of religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.58,0:12:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The transcendent God is elsewhere in time and space.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.82,0:12:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He's back there before he threw the billiard ball that became the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.13,0:12:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's up there in heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.02,0:12:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's depicted as the ceiling of the Sistine Chapel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.57,0:12:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,God reaching down to man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.43,0:12:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,See, he's up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.15,0:13:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you go by Genesis, God appeared, created the world, and then apparently disappeared in the interim.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.93,0:13:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So God was, and even if he is, he's up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.25,0:13:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So that makes you feel separated from God, does it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.53,0:13:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You're down here and he's up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.97,0:13:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Created the universe and disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.53,0:13:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Left you rolling out there all on your lonesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.30,0:13:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is infinite is always.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.49,0:13:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Has no beginning, has no end, has no location.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.15,0:13:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization I had in the snowbank, and we'll confirm the truth of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.72,0:13:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to confirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.53,0:13:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That which I am existed before all worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.77,0:13:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That which I am will still be after all worlds have disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.93,0:14:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just out of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.73,0:14:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity arises out of the Godhead, arises divinity as creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.25,0:14:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And first there is the Godhead, out of which arises God as creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.01,0:14:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And God's creation manifests as the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.94,0:14:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But each one is a different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.68,0:14:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.05,0:14:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Godness arises out of the Godhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.87,0:14:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.03,0:14:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.25,0:14:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.79,0:14:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I am struggling with trying to stay aware of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.85,0:14:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In the busyness of my day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.91,0:14:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I may start out in the morning making a commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.53,0:14:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And then by the end of the day, I see that I wasn't even aware of God all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.98,0:14:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you weren't thinking about God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.72,0:15:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Awareness is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.16,0:15:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking about is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.58,0:15:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Awareness is present or you wouldn't be complaining that you'd stop thinking about God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.62,0:15:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't confuse thinking about God with awareness of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.84,0:15:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of awareness of God, you're distressed that you, you know, stop thinking about God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.46,0:15:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.28,0:15:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there are some people who think about God all the time, but it doesn't do much good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.43,0:15:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's other people who only think of God rarely, but it seems to do them a lot of good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.73,0:15:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you make your declaration for the day in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.47,0:15:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.97,0:15:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Your declaration for your life and your declaration for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.70,0:15:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And you ask God for forgiveness that you can't function within the world and mentally keep repeating his name all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.01,0:15:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do that if you're in an ashram.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.79,0:15:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.29,0:15:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.63,0:16:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.13,0:16:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to thank you for being a teacher and all you've done and all you are doing for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.47,0:16:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So just thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.55,0:16:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.43,0:16:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.91,0:16:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.87,0:16:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he brought a bowling ball with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.70,0:16:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Down the alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.04,0:16:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, I wish to extend my love and gratitude to yourself and Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.56,0:16:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.70,0:16:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.00,0:16:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, would you be willing to muscle test if I am dual or multiple personality?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.94,0:16:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll ask permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.86,0:16:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.18,0:16:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.86,0:16:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You suspect it could be a factor based on the occurrence yesterday, possibly recontextualizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.38,0:16:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he's talking about different levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.86,0:17:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't really have two personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.94,0:17:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, he is not a compartmentalized personality, because you wouldn't be complaining about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they usually do not suspect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.78,0:17:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.74,0:17:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.65,0:17:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.09,0:17:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,People who worry about it, they don't have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.21,0:17:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What they really mean is different moods, different states of consciousness, but not different personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.22,0:17:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has their upside and their downside, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.62,0:17:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.84,0:17:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.36,0:17:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.47,0:17:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.50,0:18:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We kid around.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.06,0:18:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.72,0:18:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.10,0:18:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If time is an illusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.50,0:18:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,how come there is a progression from birth to childhood to adulthood to old age?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.46,0:18:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're, you're conjecturing something called time in which this occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.60,0:18:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It would occur without the conjecture of time and see this go into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.40,0:18:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need time to explain that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.92,0:18:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd you come up with time?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.78,0:18:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a superimposition and you're saying this is happening in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.88,0:18:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of like a track at the bottom of a TV program.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.28,0:18:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.34,0:18:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.40,0:18:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they call that track that I've done at the bottom?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.80,0:18:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, time gets imprinted on, it gets imprinted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.40,0:18:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not innate to experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.14,0:18:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you let go resisting the experience of time, it disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.52,0:19:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of time, which is subliminal all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.13,0:19:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If you become conscious of it and let go resisting it, what will happen is you'll disappear time, which is sometimes handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.27,0:19:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Got to drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.39,0:19:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Phoenix to Sedona and it takes place experientially in, uh, less than a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.82,0:19:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You just leave Phoenix and you're in Sedona and there's no memory of, uh, you know, uh, time progression.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.48,0:19:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, that's one of the fastest ways to transcend the ego is to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.92,0:19:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,To let go of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.58,0:19:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Time imprinting and let go resisting this, the experience of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.16,0:19:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you let go resisting it, it will eventually all of a sudden disappear and then you're in timelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.53,0:19:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.03,0:19:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you constantly have to ask people, you know, what time, how much time we got left here and would the body then stop aging?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.59,0:19:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.91,0:20:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The body goes on by itself, but he doesn't eat by time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.25,0:20:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It eats when he thinks it needs to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.38,0:20:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can let go needing to eat too, you know, and then somebody has to remind you, you better eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.46,0:20:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always somebody nuisancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.74,0:20:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You're telling you it's time to eat all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.90,0:20:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I ate Tuesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.46,0:20:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the hell I want to eat now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.70,0:20:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.36,0:20:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they complain you're too skinny.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.92,0:20:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you can't keep them happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.16,0:20:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.74,0:20:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.24,0:20:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You, your work and research has really changed our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.70,0:20:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.94,0:20:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.30,0:20:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Time is a fast track to transcending the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.41,0:20:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.04,0:21:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.34,0:21:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Time is a super imposition, which is projected on to phenomenal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.74,0:21:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not intrinsic to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.24,0:21:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.73,0:21:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people who live in different time dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.00,0:21:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There are different cultures in which time is experienced differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.46,0:21:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you when I was in Ecuador, there was two planes out a week from, uh, there were two, two planes a week out of Ecuador, Wednesday and Saturday or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.42,0:21:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got there for the Wednesday plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.98,0:21:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They said the Wednesday plane was leaving till Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.76,0:21:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And in Ecuador, 10,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.36,0:21:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,10,000 feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.20,0:21:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It just didn't make a darn bit of difference that happened in Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.22,0:22:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have been all of a sudden, but in Ecuador, they sort of live beyond time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.55,0:22:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, I told you before in the middle of the airport in Ecuador, yeah, is a clock, which stopped many years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.37,0:22:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody bothered to fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.60,0:22:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Wednesday plane is not leaving till Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.04,0:22:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, okay, Saturday went back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.48,0:22:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I was there at quarter 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.34,0:22:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Plane was going to leave at 12 and all of a sudden there was one plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.22,0:22:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One, one airplane on the whole, in the whole airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.88,0:22:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, all of a sudden this engine shut down, uh, because it was siesta time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.26,0:22:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They shut the engines down on this plane from 12 till three o'clock at three o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.52,0:22:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Brrng, the siesta time was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.24,0:22:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The engines started up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.12,0:22:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I got aboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.84,0:22:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We took off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.22,0:22:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't have a slight, didn't feel the slightest stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.91,0:22:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.93,0:22:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow in the never, never landed at 10,000 feet in Ecuador.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.00,0:22:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.39,0:22:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that on your video.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.51,0:22:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.13,0:23:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wonderful to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.19,0:23:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.59,0:23:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Live.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.25,0:23:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No distress.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.12,0:23:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.78,0:23:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.44,0:23:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here to thank you with my respects.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.44,0:23:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.62,0:23:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You just sort of transcend time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.41,0:23:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So no matter what happens, just pretend you're in Ecuador.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.26,0:23:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Time doesn't make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.16,0:23:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I loved Ecuador for that reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.42,0:23:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like never, never land.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.91,0:23:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope I can remember my question.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.11,0:23:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.31,0:23:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been, um, I've been in a happy place for quite a few years and suddenly I come
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.52,0:23:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,up upon retiring from my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.02,0:24:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been in a happy place for years?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.68,0:24:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.68,0:24:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.68,0:24:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,She's retired.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.13,0:24:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, retired.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.13,0:24:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you meant a psychically happy place.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.37,0:24:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.37,0:24:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.94,0:24:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, so this retirement seems to be bringing on, and I'm thinking it might be my animal
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.66,0:24:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,fear of the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.22,0:24:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.22,0:24:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I identified with that, and I got in a very bad place from my perspective, and I
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.30,0:24:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,just.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.30,0:24:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean like health worries, financial worries, or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.30,0:24:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Financial worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.30,0:24:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Financial worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.30,0:24:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.30,0:24:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you just get to be poor, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.34,0:24:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.34,0:24:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And, and what's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.34,0:24:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.34,0:24:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.34,0:24:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.34,0:24:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then you live like a poor person lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.34,0:24:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.34,0:24:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No spending money.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.34,0:24:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.34,0:24:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't spend any money for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.43,0:24:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you go find another job.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.43,0:24:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you can do, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.43,0:24:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.43,0:24:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And all those things are part of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.43,0:24:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.43,0:24:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.62,0:24:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All those things were kind of, um, not in my awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.04,0:25:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just aware of all of the negatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.70,0:25:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All of the what?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.70,0:25:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Negatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.79,0:25:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you were writing these negative scenarios.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.71,0:25:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.71,0:25:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.71,0:25:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What you do is you surrender all these negative scenarios.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.95,0:25:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.53,0:25:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You, uh, are homeless, you live on a park bench, you cover yourself up with newspapers,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.38,0:25:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,let it be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.84,0:25:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you're hungry, you go to the bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.56,0:25:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They always have tea and cookies there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.02,0:25:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you, uh, borrow the Wall Street Journal from the bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.49,0:25:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And you go out in the park and read the Wall Street Journal and eat your cookies and coffee
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.61,0:25:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,from the bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.61,0:25:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.61,0:25:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you hang out with the bag ladies and, uh, jolly them up and see how they make
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.27,0:25:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a living.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.27,0:25:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So pretty soon you get a basket yourself.
